observations.recommendation:
We recommended and management agreed to: 

(a) draw the lease contract for all existing market stallholders; 




(b) fast track the approval of the New Revenue Code of Pantabangan by the Sangguniang Bayan so that they could finally apply the new competitive rates, hence, increasing their income from rentals from market stalls.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive :
require Ms. Gonzales to account for the 92 missing ORs and return the amount collected totaling ₱1,495,993.11, as adjusted and deposit the same to the PAMES account.  Likewise, Ms. Barcelona should also return the amount of ₱994,215.51;
require written explanation from Ms. Gonzales and Ms. Barcelona on why they used the collections in paying obligations of the municipality despite the fact that they will violate Section 69 of PD No. 1445;
give warning to Ms. Grospe that repetition of such negligence  will be also be dealt accordingly;
relieve  all concerned accountable officers from holding position involving money and property accountability; and
file criminal or any appropriate charges against the erring accountable officials for the above unaccounted collections and accountable forms.
